on Valentine’s Day as it is any other day of the year.</p><p class="" style="margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(28, 29, 29); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; letter-spacing: 1.3px; text-align: start;"><br></p><p class="" style="margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(28, 29, 29); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; letter-spacing: 1.3px; text-align: start;">Nothing starts a good day like a nourishing breakfast – and on a day where so many plans can be up in the air, why not get one thing right and begin with something good for you, and for your tastebuds! Get in the Valentine’s Day spirit with heart shaped pancakes, plenty of berries, or a yogurt parfait filled with nutrients from things like walnuts or chia seeds.&nbsp;</p></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" id="e-1606180178625" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1606180178625"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-weight: 700; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 35px; letter-spacing: 0.75px;"><br></span></p><p><font face="Montserrat"><b>2. Netflix &amp; Chill</b></font></p></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" id="e-1606180241379" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1606180241379"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><br></p><p class="" style="margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(28, 29, 29); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; letter-spacing: 1.3px; text-align: start;">A classic that’s here to stay. What better way to celebrate a night-in on Valentine’s Day than to press play on your favorite TV show series or movie? With so many choices — romantic comedies, thrillers, musicals, dramas — you’ll be sure to get a good laugh (or cry) while relaxing for the night.</p></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" id="e-1606180274929" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1606180274929"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-weight: 700; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 35px; letter-spacing: 0.75px;"><br></span></p><p><font face="Montserrat"><b>3. Treat Yourself to a Facial</b></font></p></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" id="e-1606180453146" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1606180453146"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><br></p><p class="" style="margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(28, 29, 29); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; letter-spacing: 1.3px; text-align: start;">Valentine’s Day falls on February 14 of every year, which is also a date that’s set right in the heart of Winter. Treat yourself to a facial to rejuvenate your skin, keeping it fresh and glowing this Winter season.&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(28, 29, 29); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; letter-spacing: 1.3px; text-align: start;"><br></p><p class="" style="margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(28, 29, 29); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; letter-spacing: 1.3px; text-align: start;">If your night should lead to going out this Valentine’s Day, then ditch the Netflix but schedule your facial earlier in the day, so you can prep your skin before putting on makeup.</p></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" id="e-1606180283162" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1606180283162"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-e